tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All measured parameters are within normal limits except for a markedly elevated platelet distribution width, which may indicate increased platelet size variability, possibly due to platelet activation or turnover. No acute abnormalities are evident in renal, metabolic, or hematologic parameters. Correlation with clinical context and follow-up of platelet indices is recommended.
